Subject: Meeting with Bloomin Brands

JR,

Please see notes below from my meeting with Donagh Herlihy and Dolf Berle from Bloomin Brands today. Overall, I
think it went very well but they did have quite a few questions around Shift4 and the product. I did my best to
answer/position everything appropriately but you may have more insight here. I did tell them that we are working
with Jared to have him reach out to their CEO to discuss the partnership in more detail as well

Talking Points:
•	 Donagh has been at Bloomin for about 2 years and came from what he referred to has "high growth tech
companies", the latest one being ShopKeep. Dolf also came from a previous high growth background.
•	 Bloomin Brands has a large focus on facing the future. They realize guests expectations are changing to the
likes of Amazon, Apple, etc.
•	 They've made major investments in the following areas to prepare for future shifts
    o Revamp of Online Ordering System
    o Investment in Kitchen Display Systems
    o Handhelds in testing across 36 locations

•	 Dolf mentioned that their approach to technology is partnering with vendors that solve specific problems as
best in breed as opposed to full stack systems.
•	 Biggest pain points:
    o Multiple merchants. They have 5 different merchant accounts
         Reconciliation
         Funding
         Chargebacks
    o Number of vendors is a headache
    o Multiple VARs
    o Currently use First Data for processing but feel as though "they aren't the company they used to be".
    He didn't go into many specifics here
•	 Questions
    o Shift4 Model
         "Are you a technology company? A Payments company? Both?"
    o Shift4 Products
         Is your gateway EMV certified to First Data. He mentioned they have pain points with this
         Do you support only specific hardware outside of your POS systems - Verifone, Ingenico,
        IDTech, etc
         Do you have reporting on the gateway? How robust is it?
         Our current provider gives complete transparency/visibility into interchange rates received.
        Does yours?
         Are there any industries you don't support?
            •	 I mentioned gaming/gambling may be tough
         Do you support American Express OptBlue
         Do you have a partner program outside of VARs. Can technology companies integrate into the
        Shift4 gateway?
    o SkyTab
         Does SkyTab support pay at table AND payments on KDS stations?
            •	 They ask this because they have an initiative to send all payments through the KDS.
            They want to know if they should use BOTH SkyTab and KDS simultaneously.
         Does SkyTab work with the Oracle Hosted model?
         What is the cost?

Thanks,
Taylor Laurer | Director, ISV Integrations
